cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CY, cs.GT 

This paper deals with secure communication and cryptography, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of set systems and combinatorics, which could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of PSMT protocols for secure communication could also fall under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the importance of reducing reliance on untrusted computers, which could be classified under cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper proposes solutions for both single and multi-seat elections, which could be classified under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
